Seventeen people were injured after a crash on Watson Highway in Tongaat on Wednesday morning. “The Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) members were dispatched to the scene and upon arrival found a Toyota Quantum and a Mahindra SUV lying on its side,” Rusa spokesperson Prem Balram said. Balram said it was established that the fully loaded taxi was travelling in the direction of Tongaat, when it collided into the side of the Mahindra SUV that was turning onto the south bound lane of the N2 from Watson Highway. The injured were treated on scene for moderate to serious injuries before being transported to hospital by medics from a private ambulance service. 